    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix buffer overflow in TX beamforming PRG processing\n\n### Summary\nThe `pack_nr_tx_beamforming_pdu` function in nr_fapi_p7.c was vulnerable to buffer overflow when processing PRG lists. The static array size for `prgs_list` was set to 1 (`NFAPI_MAX_NUM_PRGS`) but the 5G NR specification allows up to 275 PRGs. When `num_prgs` exceeded 1, out-of-bounds memory access occurred during both packing and unpacking operations.\n\nThis fix increases the array size to support the full specification range and adds proper input validation.\n\n### Changes\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/nfapi/public_inc/nfapi_nr_interface_scf.h`: Changed `NFAPI_MAX_NUM_PRGS` from 1 to 275\n- `nfapi/open-nFAPI/fapi/src/nr_fapi_p7.c`: Added null pointer checks and range validation in both pack/unpack functions, fixed incorrect \"RX Beamforming\" comments\n\n### Reproduction\nTo reproduce the issue:\n1. Call `pack_nr_tx_beamforming_pdu` with a beamforming PDU where `num_prgs` > 1\n2. Observe memory corruption or segmentation fault due to out-of-bounds array access\n3. Similar behavior occurs with `unpack_nr_tx_beamforming_pdu` when processing packed data with `num_prgs` > 1\n\nThe fix ensures that valid specification-compliant values (1-275) for `num_prgs` are properly handled without memory safety issues.\n"
}